<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Large species (10.3-13 mm) with wide dark brown abdomen and yellow-orange maculae on lateral sides of tergum 2 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="F24" captionText="Figure 24. Merodon medium sp. nov., abdomen, dorsal view. A male B female. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure24" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377385" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">24A, B</figureCitation>
); basoflagellomere elongated, ca. 2.5 times longer than broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Antenna. A Merodon hirsutus, outer side, lateral view, male B Merodon hirsutus, inner side, lateral view, male C Merodon hirsutus, dorsal view, male D Merodon hirsutus, outer side, lateral view, female E Merodon kawamurae, outer side, lateral view, male F Merodon kawamurae, inner side, lateral view, male G Merodon kawamurae, dorsal view, male H Merodon kawamurae, outer side, lateral view, female I Merodon medium sp. nov., outer side, lateral view, male J Merodon medium sp. nov., outer side, lateral view, female. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377380" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">19 I, J</figureCitation>
,); metafemur incrassate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. A, B metaleg, C, D metatrochanter, metafemur and metatibia, lateral view. A Merodon kawamurae, male B Merodon kawamurae, female C Merodon medium sp. nov., male D Merodon medium sp. nov., female. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377383" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">22C, D</figureCitation>
); terga 2-4 with conspicuous microtrichose fasciae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="F24" captionText="Figure 24. Merodon medium sp. nov., abdomen, dorsal view. A male B female. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure24" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377385" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">24A, B</figureCitation>
). Similar to some populations of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann in Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon serrulatus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Merodon serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but clearly differs in shape of abdomen: relation between maximum width of tergum 2 and its medial length is 3.3 in male and 3.5 in female of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. medium" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="medium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. medium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. compared with 2.3 in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. serrulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male and 2.7 in female; male genitalia: anterior surstyle lobe with concave margin in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. medium" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="medium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. medium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Male genitalia, surstylus, lateral view. A Merodon serrulatus, Spain B Merodon serrulatus, France C Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Pindos) D Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Olympos) E Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Peloponnese) F Merodon serrulatus, Montenegro G Merodon serrulatus, Russia H Merodon medium sp. nov. G, H margin of anterior surstyle lobe marked with arrow. Abbreviation: bp-basolateral protrusion. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377367" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">6H</figureCitation>
: marked with arrow), convex in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. serrulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Male genitalia, surstylus, lateral view. A Merodon serrulatus, Spain B Merodon serrulatus, France C Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Pindos) D Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Olympos) E Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Peloponnese) F Merodon serrulatus, Montenegro G Merodon serrulatus, Russia H Merodon medium sp. nov. G, H margin of anterior surstyle lobe marked with arrow. Abbreviation: bp-basolateral protrusion. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377367" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">6G</figureCitation>
: marked with arrow); apical microtrichose area of anterior surstyle lobe 2.5 times broader than long in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. medium" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="medium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. medium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Male genitalia, surstylus, lateral view. A Merodon serrulatus, Spain B Merodon serrulatus, France C Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Pindos) D Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Olympos) E Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Peloponnese) F Merodon serrulatus, Montenegro G Merodon serrulatus, Russia H Merodon medium sp. nov. G, H margin of anterior surstyle lobe marked with arrow. Abbreviation: bp-basolateral protrusion. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377367" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">6G</figureCitation>
: al), less than one time in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. serrulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Male genitalia, surstylus, lateral view. A Merodon serrulatus, Spain B Merodon serrulatus, France C Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Pindos) D Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Olympos) E Merodon serrulatus, Greece (Peloponnese) F Merodon serrulatus, Montenegro G Merodon serrulatus, Russia H Merodon medium sp. nov. G, H margin of anterior surstyle lobe marked with arrow. Abbreviation: bp-basolateral protrusion. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377367" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">6G</figureCitation>
: al); molecular data and distribution (
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. medium" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="medium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. medium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is an endemic to the island of Crete in Greece).
</paragraph>
