<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Medium (middle, center) refers to the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
distribution, being the only taxon of the group found on Crete, in the middle of Mediterranean Sea.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vujic, Likov &amp; Radenkovic" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon medium" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Merodon medium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is endemic to the Greek island of Crete (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Distribution map of Merodon serrulatus species group." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377368" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Preferred environment: forest/open ground; evergreen oak forest, dry 
<taxonomicName class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pinus" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Pinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forest; scrub with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Pistacia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pistacia lentiscus" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lentiscus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Pistacia lentiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.; well-vegetated, unimproved grassland. Flowers visited: 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Ornithogalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ornithogalum" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ornithogalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Potentilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Potentilla" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Potentilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Thymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thymus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Thymus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. Flight period: May.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
